This paper presents a neural model for text summarization, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) field. The use of neural networks suggests that it could belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves both extraction and compression of sentences, which could fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of neural models for scoring compressions could also suggest the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The evaluation of the model's performance using ROUGE, a common metric in NLP, could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the use of syntactic compression could suggest the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
